13
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,260
Mari Tere told me...

14
00:02:23,660 --> 00:02:25,400
she went to the pines
at the beach...

15
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:28,510
with Antonio and their little one,
José Manuel.

16
00:02:29,810 --> 00:02:33,880
They saw a light in the distance
and went to see what it was.

17
00:02:34,390 --> 00:02:35,910
As they got closer...

18
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:40,070
there was this smell of flowers
that became stronger.

19
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:44,140
They got to the rocks
in the pine grove.

20
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,490
It was all lit up.

21
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,310
They saw the figure
of the Virgin Mary in the light.

22
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:56,570
Mari Tere says...

23
00:02:57,420 --> 00:03:01,030
that the Virgin
pointed at José Manuel.

24
00:03:01,350 --> 00:03:04,450
She was like that for a while,
then the lights disappeared.

25
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:07,380
She says that night...

26
00:03:08,050 --> 00:03:10,920
the Virgin got into her son's body.

27
00:03:11,450 --> 00:03:13,110
And they've found out...

28
00:03:13,420 --> 00:03:16,150
if you put your ear
to the back of his neck,

29
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,500
you can hear the Virgin talk.

30
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,750
Don't threaten me! Don't!

31
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:37,410
Don't you dare!

32
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,640
How's things, Mari Carmen?

33
00:03:40,110 --> 00:03:41,940
Getting by, Trini.

34
